Beyond the Night (Christian Movie)


Beyond the Night is a family film produced by Unusual Films in 1983 that tells the true story of John and Bettie Dreisbach, a medical missionary couple in Africa. To them came the injured and the sick. The word soon spread across the desert, and their patients became a multitude. Above all, the Light of the World, Jesus Christ, was revealed by his faithful witness to people who dwelt in darkness. The couple are loved by the local people but not by the evil muslim authorities who don't like that they're preaching the Gospel of Jesus Christ. 

The courage and faith of this couple in the face of strong persecution will challenge the hearts of both young and old. A good resource for Bible and missions training. Suitable for upper elementary, teens, and adults.

Runtime: 63 mins
Language: English
Year: 1983
Quality: 8/10 
Format: avi format 

